.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-7::.
House: tower, victorian, cottage, cape-cod, palace, farmhouse
The people use 6 different means of transport: bike, boat, quad-bike, roller, tram, van
1. the person driving the roller is the person driving the roller##1
2. the person driving the van is on the left of the tower house##1
3. the tower house is between the palace house and the cape-cod house##2
4. the cape-cod house is the person driving the van##1
5. the farmhouse house is on the left of the cape-cod house##1
6. the palace house is between the person driving the roller and the person driving the tram##2
7. the person driving the roller is on the right of the person driving the bike##1
8. the victorian house is on the right of the person driving the roller##1
9. the person driving the boat is on the right of the cottage house##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1     |   2    |   3   |    4    |     5     |    6    |
| House       | farmhouse | cape-cod | tower | palace | cottage | victorian |
| Transport   | quad-bike | van    | tram  | bike    | roller    | boat    |

